deposit(address,uint256,uint256).details: is deposited data is a preset than user will retrieve special NFT

params.priceTarget: price target to reach to be able to withdraw
params.token: address of token to deposit. address(0) for ETH

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.tokenId: tokenId of the NFT (deposit) to get the URI for

returns._0: tokenURI is generated dynamically based on deposit data using URIUtils

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw(uint256).details: user is only able to withdraw if price target is reached

params.tokenId: tokenId of the NFT to withdraw

deposits(uint256).notice: returns deposit data for a given tokenId

getPresetId(address,uint256,uint256).notice: generate preset id from deposit data

isWithdrawn(uint256).notice: returns true if deposit is withdrawn

presets(bytes32).notice: returns true if it (deposit data) is a preset

tokenURI(uint256).notice: returns tokenURI for a given tokenId

documentation.text: @notice returns true if it (deposit data) is a preset
@notice returns true if deposit is withdrawn
@notice returns deposit data for a given tokenId
@notice generate preset id from deposit data
